<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101681324089256></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101681324089256><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=101681324089256>RE: Which Specialisation at level 30?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=101681324089256#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=63996><span id=Scholar>Lord chking</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>71 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Mar 22nd 11:10 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.42]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Alteration, in my opinion, is the way to go. It saves you on ports, healing, and buffs -- the meat of a druid's career. However, if you're a nuking druid or a kiter, evocation or conjuration may be for you. I let Tunare and Fate decide, and just put one point in each and cast as I normally did. As I guessed, Alteration bubbled to the top and hit 50 before the others did. But, don't worry if you regret your choice later on -- there is an easy quest that will reset your specializations and allow you to choose again:<br><br><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=711" target=_new>http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=711</a><br><br>Happy hunting!<br>&nbsp;<br>-- <br>[Druid] Lambeau Farstrider (Human)<br>[Rogue] Gripp Tinkersnout (Gnome)<br>[Shaman] Tashtego (Barbarian)<br>&lt;Tragic Heroes&gt; -- Saryrn</td></tr>
