	   <tr><td colspan=2>I was introduced to EQ by some friends who were on the Rallos Zek server so my fist halfling Druid born into a world of fear and carnage.... <br><br>But I was a roleplaying pacifist!<br><br>I cant tell you how many times I was rooted, nuked and robbed of my leather tunic in the hills of Misty. <br><br>After a while I would just sit calmly and chat with my assasin while he slashed me to bits. I'd say things like &quot;Are we having fun?&quot; &quot;I've put everything in my pack so dont expect to get loot.&quot; <br>&quot;Were you abused as a child?&quot;<br><br>But It was my fault for being on the wrong server. I never got past 10th level from all the dying. <br><br>Now all my characters live on Cazic thule. I am happily 16th and growing fast!&nbsp;&nbsp;I enjoy the ability to wear my items with out fear of being killed for them around every corner.<br>Also - A halfling druid is great to roleplay with. I love telling jokes and being a jolly outdoorsman. <br><br>I have found it easy to group if you snare and back up heal. Also DOT is handy for the big mobs and if you have a good weapon - get in there! Just be sure to pull away if you are targetted. Your HP and AC are nothing compared to a tank.<br>Our DDs are  less powerful than other casters but can be helpful if you want to take down something quick ( like when too many are pulled- ever happen to you?)<br><br>And I havent even mentioned SOW!<br><br>Well there is a lot more but Im only 16 and wont pretend to be wiser than I am. ( port! )<br><br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Hobenroby Thistlefoot<br>Halfling Druid<br>Cazic Thule</td></tr>
