<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101604887425766></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101604887425766><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=101604887425766>RE: Starting a Druid`</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=101604887425766#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=73409><span id=Scholar>Mistress ancarett</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>107 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Mar 13th 2:50 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.54]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The primary spell-casting stat for a druid is wisdom (as with clerics and shaman). So wisdom would be preferable. Other statistics that can help include stamina (for more hitpoints), strength (to hit harder while you melee at low levels, to carry more), agility and dexterity. Some druids also like charisma, it helps in charming animals.<br><br>As for race, it is up to you. The possible races are half elf, halfling, human and wood elf. Only humans start with no night vision but there is a level 1 druid spell that summons a light source and at higher levels you can get really good infravision/ultravision items. Halflings and Wood Elves have the best starting wisdom, so they are very popular choices. Any race will work out: I know Level 60 druids of all races, so choose what works best for you.<br>&nbsp;<br>-- Yseulte/Ancarett<br>Veeshan Server</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
