	   <tr><td colspan=2>What wisdom you havent doesnt really matter unless you know how to fight. <br>Im a druid of the 45th season , my wisdom is only 186 and I have plenty of mana to quad kite with ease. You dont need to max out 200+ wisdom . Theres no big need till you hit your 50's, and by then your not going to be going after just wisdom items anyways. At the point your are going to be going after quest armor which include many stats into it. <br><br>So save your money for spells and only pick up an item when you need it. <br><br>At lvl 20 you should have about 130 wisdom.<br>At lvl 30 you should have about 150 wisdom.<br>at lvl 40 you should have about 170 wisdom. <br>at lvl 50 you should have about 190-200 wisdom. <br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
